Class NeuralMap

  • java.lang.Object
    • neurality.NeuralMap

  • public class NeuralMap
extends java.lang.Object
    The "blueprint" class for neural networks. Maps do not contain actual neurons, rather they contain the information to build a neural network.
    Author:
    James

    • Constructor Detail

      • NeuralMap

        public NeuralMap(NeuralRegistry registry,
                 int width,
                 int height,
                 int inputs,
                 int outputs)
        Generate a new map from scratch.
        Parameters:
        registry - The registry to draw instantiatable types and parameters from.
        width - The number of hidden layers in this map.
        height - The maximum size of all hidden layers.
        inputs - The size of the input layer (i.e. the number of inputs).
        outputs - The size of the output layer (i.e. the number of outputs).

      • NeuralMap

        public NeuralMap(NeuralMap template,
                 int radiation)
        Generate this map as a clone of another.
        Parameters:
        template - The map to clone.
        radiation - The number of times to mutate the new map. A value of 0 will result in the clone being identical to its template.
